reviewText: Very Good - very short, but effective

Good, basic introduction. Some of the terminology seems to be academic jargon-ese, where they come up with complicated names for simple things. But this was very good to show my children, as they go off to college and onwards. The last couple of the lectures were very good, dealing with workplace, interviewing, etc.
BTW - it's best if you try to ignore the constant arm-waving of the lecturer. Otherwise, it gets distracting.
